{"displayTopicName":"Hebrew definite article","topicTokens":[{"text":"Hebrew definite article","type":"text"}],"paragraphsBySubtopic":{"Hebrew definite article":[{"tokens":[{"text":"Hebrew has an entity called a ","type":"text"},{"text":"definite article","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"definite article","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Definite_Article","enclosingTopic":"Hebrew definite article","enclosingSubtopic":"Hebrew definite article"},{"text":", as do many languages.","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"Definite articles are used to refer to things that are already known to the reader.","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"In Hebrew, the definite article presents as a ה-prefix before a noun, usually pronounced הַ, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"ha","type":"text"}]},{"text":", e.g. as in הַכֶּלֶב, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"hakelev","type":"text"}]},{"text":", “the dog.”","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"The term in Hebrew for “definite article” is ה\"א הַיְּדִיעָה, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"hay hayediah","type":"text"}]},{"text":", literally “the hay of knowledge,” i.e. because it is used to refer to something that is already known to the reader.","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"tokens":[{"text":"Sometimes, the הַ gets combined with ","type":"text"},{"text":"the prefix ב","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"the prefix ב","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Prefix_ב","enclosingTopic":"Hebrew definite article","enclosingSubtopic":"Hebrew definite article"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"text":"the prefix ל","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"the prefix ל","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Prefix_ל","enclosingTopic":"Hebrew definite article","enclosingSubtopic":"Hebrew definite article"},{"text":", and becomes a בַ or לַ, meaning “in the” or “to the,” e.g. adding ב before הַבַּיִת becoming בַּבַּיִת, “in the house.”","type":"text"}],"type":"text-line"},{"text":"Aramaic also has a ","type":"text"},{"text":"definite article","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"definite article","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Aramaic_definite_article","enclosingTopic":"Hebrew definite article","enclosingSubtopic":"Hebrew definite article"},{"text":", but it is an א-suffix not a ה-prefix, as in עָלְמָא (","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"alma,","type":"text"}]},{"text":" “the world”)","type":"text"}]}}